<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-19748] Memory leak using range scans</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-19748</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We introduced a regression bug in AK 4.1.0 release, when range scans are use. We are leaking some metrics/sensors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eduwerc&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eduwerc&quot;&gt;eduwerc&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hermankj&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hermankj&quot;&gt;hermankj&lt;/a&gt; for reporting this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anybody who is using iterator, ie, any type of all/rang/prefix scan etc is affected. Note that certain DSL operators like session-windows, sliding-windows, stream-stream joins, and FK-join all use range scans internally, so the number of affected users is expected to be quite high.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
